{
    "language_insights": [
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_1",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: هَوَىٰ – يَهْوِي means to fall. It is something falling from a very high place, we use the word هَوَىٰ and it is typically used in Arabic literature for the falling of stars.<br> ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "هَوَىٰ"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_11",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: الْفُؤَادُ refers to the emotional or overwhelmed heart.  <br> ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "ٱلْفُؤَادُ"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_22",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: ضِيزَىٰ means something that is unjust and twisted. <br> ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "ضِيزَىٰٓ"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_30",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: مَبْلَغُ means the extent or sum of something and refers to how far something reaches i.e., in terms of quantity or amount.<br> ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "مَبْلَغُهُم"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_32",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: اللَّمَمَ can refer to those small actions that can lead to major sins. It can also refer to minor sins.   <br> ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "ٱللَّمَمَ"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_37",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: وَفَّىٰ means to fulfil one’s promise or duty. <br> ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "وَفَّىٰٓ"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_41",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: الْأَوْفَىٰ means the “most full and complete”.<br> ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "ٱلْأَوْفَىٰ"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_42",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>  <br>Derivative: الْمُنْتَهَىٰ means the final destination or the place that it all comes to an end.<br> ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "ٱلْمُنتَهَىٰ"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_5",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>- شَدِيدُ الْقُوَىٰ – The one possessing intense strength or power, referring to Jibreel (as). <br> ",
                    "insight_type": "phrase",
                    "arabic_part": "شَدِيدُ الْقُوَىٰ"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_53",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: الْمُؤْتَفِكَةَ means to be completely overturned upon itself or turned upside down in reference to the town of the nation of Lut (as). <br> ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "وَٱلْمُؤْتَفِكَةَ"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_57",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: أَزِفَتِ from أَزِفَ means to come down and land, arrive or occur. It means to draw near and be close in terms of time.<br> ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "أَزِفَتِ"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_6",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: مِرَّةٍ refers to a strength and power that does not diminish.<br> ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "مِرَّةٍ"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_61",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: سَامِدُونَ means to be engrossed in entertainment, amusement and heedlessness.<br> ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "سَٰمِدُونَ"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_8",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: دَنَا to approach by descending or lowering. It implies slowness as opposed to swooping down suddenly.",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "دَنَا"
                },
                {
                    "part_num": 2,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: تَدَلَّىٰ to hang in a suspended manner or hover. It is used in Arabic to describe a fruit hanging from a tree.<br> ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "فَتَدَلَّىٰ"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "formatted_ayah_ref": "53_9",
            "details": [
                {
                    "part_num": 1,
                    "text": "<br>Derivative: قَابَ means the distance of referring to a very short distance and used in reference to the spans of bows. ",
                    "insight_type": "word",
                    "arabic_part": "قَابَ"
                },
                {
                    "part_num": 2,
                    "text": "<br>- قَابَ قَوْسَيْنِ – “The distance of two bows” is an expression to mean that something is very close either in terms of distance or in terms of time.<br> ",
                    "insight_type": "phrase",
                    "arabic_part": "قَابَ قَوْسَيْنِ"
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}